<gmapID>0x80dc09936c896743:0xee8af515780ca0ce<//gmapID><Review>Eat here.  I 'd previously enjoyed their Grilled Chicken Cobb Salad at the Mission Valley location and wanted to have it again while at the One Paseo boutique outdoor mall.  This is the salad of my dreams.   It's a huge amount of food for a very modest price and it's loaded with goodies.  The grilled chicken is mostly thigh meat with very crispy skin and so tender inside.  Intensely flavorful, thanks to all the seasonings and probably too much salt.  But hey.  All the other ingredients were top quality and very generous as well.  Bacon was also crispy-tender in nice chunks.  Tomatoes so tomato-y.  Perfect amount of eggy tarragon dressing.  Really too much food for a normal lunch but I couldn't stop eating.  The only slight miss was the grilled slice of sourdough that came with it.  Probably sat a bit too long after grilling but still edible.  I'll pass on that next time.  But their mint lemonade was a perfect accompaniment to the salad.  Very tart and very sweet at the same time.

It's also a very pleasant place to be.  Super friendly and helpful staff.  An array of heaters outside for chilly days but seating indoors as well.  Very clean and attractive.  Window shopping along pretty One Paseo is a nice bonus.  There is ample free parking in two garage structures.  What more could you want?<//Review>< response>

They opened this place about six month ago. The whole complex is new.

The place is very clean, light, plenty of seating, with good fresh food. The menu is pretty rich and service is prompt.

Review Update 8/6/20

< Review>
No frills lube shop. All the guys are friendly, very efficient, always do good work and check all the fluids tire pressure etc etc. Lines can be long, but they work through it pretty quick. Half the cost of Jiffy Lube. They don't vaccuum your floors, but I think that's worth 50% less. They never try to upsell, just let you know if they come across anything. I drive 15 miles to get my oil changed here. Every time.< /Review>

<user_id>112955339855841142176<//user_id><username>Kyle L</username><time>1546565494369< /time><rating>5<//rating><Review>Nice assortment of new and used punk rock and metal vinyl. Both genres of which I am fond of. ü§ò<//Review>< Pics>

< Date>
1552634452305</Date>
<Rating>5<//Rating><user_id>107091113752832712952<//user_id><Pics>None</Pics><name>Hannah Chan< /name><Response>None< /Response>< review>
This review is long overdue, but this is one of my favorite record stores of all time. Despite having a cool store and being clearly superior in his knowledge about music, the owner is extremely approachable, patient, friendly, and generally gives a sh*t about music, especially at the local level ‚Äî he is generous in allowing local bands/music acts gig inside the store space after hours from time to time, which is invaluable to the community.

Great selection of punk/rock/indie records, as well as interesting finds (once there were Charlie Brown Christmas albums). They also have some rare variants on the walls for serious collectors (sometimes rare records are posted on their Instagram as it is stocked so keep an eye out)! Nowadays, there are many record shops that don‚Äôt offer much beyond what perusing discogs can offer, with a bland, snotty, nonchalant clerk behind the counter, but Normal Records is not that. Visiting this place is a completely immersive experience and makes supporting your local/leaving the house worth it.</review>

<name>stephanie figueras< /name><time>1621898831817</time>< rating>
3< /rating>
< Review>
I will say going on a weekend was probably not the best idea for a first try on experience ever for a first time bride. The experience was not bad, but was not great. I feel like the bridal consultants are not given enough time to work with the brides. I was asked to do a survey upon booking and submit a link of my Pinterest board but it didn't seem like my consultant had any access to it. I proceeded to show her my board upon arrival to my appt. I will say she was nice but I felt very rushed the whole time. Again, probably not her fault. I do wish she may had been more helpful for a bride who really wanted the expert opinion of a consultant. I did ask to try on a specific gown which was not offered when given several dresses to try on. I actually forgot about it in the fumble of trying on like 6 dresses in 60 min. There is some fault of mine to being a bit late (8 min) to my appt, but then again I'm sure I'm not the first to be running late. When I tried on dresses there was no opportunity to see myself first in the dressing room before stepping out to a platform to show family/friends. Then I was immediately asked my opinion of the dress which was hard under pressure to give my thoughts on demand. I would not discourage going to David's Bridal, and I would say my consultant did the best she could given the time constraints. I didn't find my dress there nor did I have that emotional moment that you see on "say yes to the dress" of really falling in love with anything. But I do thank David's Bridal for helping get a little closer to knowing what I like and don't like for the next bridal appt. I book and go to.</Review>

<rating>5< /rating>< Text>
Had a wonderful Bridal Appointment at the Long Beach David's Bridal location. I was welcomed in immediately and was able to look at all the dresses for about 5 min before my consultant Sarah came over and introduced herself. She all ready had the list of dresses that I had Favorited on my online David's Bridal account. She also showed me around and pointed out new dresses that she thought I would love. This location is super clean and everyone was friendly and helpful. I was surprised by the quality of the dresses, all were so beautiful and nice. <Rating>1< /Rating><Review>I scheduled a bridesmaid fitting weeks in advance for today 11/2/19 at 10:30am. The consultant assigned to me was Theresa, an older lady who seemed very sweet. She was very disoriented as we began interacting. When I showed her the dresses I favored online, she immediately informed me which styles weren't available in store without suggesting a similar option, just plain out shut me down.

She then wrote down the style numbers & suggested I start looking for the styles & pull them myself because she had to go find the other bridesmaids she was assigned to as she had been double booked!!! My sister (the bride) bought her dress at this store & so I know that guests aren't supposed to pull their own dresses, it ruin the moment & can be a liability for the store. Theresa then proceeded to suggest that I was about 2-6 sizes larger than what I actually look like, in other words she called me fat . Before leaving me to go to her other assigned group, she mentioned that it can all go very well if we do not become too overtly demanding. While it may not have been her fault that she was assigned to two groups, her approach was unprofessional & extremely rude.

<Text>Had a very good experience with David's Bridal today, definitely worthy of a post!  I am going to be the Maid of Honor is my friends wedding just one week and a day from now.  We bought the dresses from this store on sale a few months ago.  Last week I thought I'd better get some shoes to match it so I put the dress on to determine how high of a heel I should get and I couldn't even zip the dress up.  Clearly it had shrunk in the last three months! :)   So I take it to a tailor and she tells me that unlike most gowns like this one, this one didn't have enough material to work with so she could not alter it.  Yikes!  So I went to get a second opinion somewhere else and they told me the same thing.  So I made an appointment with the alterations lady at David's Bridal in Long Beach where we bought the dress.  She said that she couldn't fix it either so they found the same dress two sizes up from the one I had.  I bought a size 8 which fit perfectly everywhere except it wouldn't zip up, too tight in the back.  They found me a 12.  Tried it on and it zipped up easily but was over all too big and too long.  The manager was calling other stores to see if they had a size 10 but no luck.  She went through every rack in the store searching for a size 10 in apple red and there it was on the last rack and out of place but she found it.  I tried it on and it fit perfectly!  They were happy to exchange it for me even though they didn't have to since we bought the dress on sale.  The cost of the alterations, being this close to the wedding would have cost  more than we paid for the dress! ($150)  So it was a good day.  Thanks David's Bridal!!<//Text>< resp>

A different woman helped me in to a dressing room. I tried on about 3 of the 5 dresses I chose until someone had asked me if a stylist had checked in, another 10 mins have passed. I replied with "No one has formally introduced themselves to me yet..." The person on the other side of my dressing room door stated she would get someone for me. I tried on the other 2 dresses and no one checked in, another 10 mins. Which, I realize, was fine as there were only other brides in the shop that evening and I am just a maid of honor. After I was done trying on the first 5 dresses I picked out, I believe, it was Heather? (woman with short hair and glasses, very kind) who finally checked in to see if I needed different sizes or other dresses. I informed her what length and color I needed for the wedding, short and Juniper. She told me this particular store did not carry many short dresses. She helped me find long dresses with the similar style of top and said they could order it a shorter length. This stylist was handling myself and a bride, so needless to say she was busy. While the stylist tried her best to keep up with giving advise and helping 2 people at the same time, the bride did take priority over my appointment. I was unable to find a dress on this visit but the stylist was very kind and helped me figure out the latest date/time of year I would need to pick and order a dress. Overall the appointment was somewhat lacking for someone who wanted some guidance and for someone who wasn't a bride. I would have liked to have someone around to help me in and out of dresses, even if they just helped me zip in. As far as customer service, the ladies I interacted with were kind but I did not get a lot of face time with any of them. It did not seem like the shop was short staffed as there were about 3 people behind the front counter at any given time and I only saw, maybe 2 people helping anyone that was in the fitting area. I wish I had a better time at this shop but I am unable to give a stellar review. I am only giving 3 stars for lovely ladies I made contact with, otherwise this review would deserve a 2 or 1 star review.<//Text></record></dataset><record>

< text>
I was very fortunate to have Uche as my stylist and Chi do my alterations. I came in on a Friday night to check out some dresses.  My appointment was for the next day. The person at the front was confusing as she made comments about availability before actually checking so we just looked around and booked a same day appointment for an hour later that night.  We found some dresses we liked,  then Uche came to greet us with her big smile and upbeat personality.  I can't tell you how much that improved our experience. Uche took us up to the register to ring us up and complete the transaction which we were interrupted by someone who wanted to take over so Uche can help her next customer,  however my issue with this is that i just spent the last hour with Uche who knows every detail of everything i need and all my dates. I felt very uneasy when they were going to have someone else step in when Uche was almost done.  Very uneasy for a bride to be.  So we asked if she can finish the transaction and then someone else stepped in to reschedule the alterations due to some changes. Anyways,  my dress came in sooner than expected for a rush order which was great,  i came in for alterations with Chi, she measured and pinned both of my dresses and had me walk in it to make sure i was comfortable,  same thing when i came to pick it up. I bought my wedding dress at Alfred Angelo in Brea. For those that don't already know, Alfred Angelo went bankrupt and shut the doors to all their stores. Thankfully I had my wedding dress at home, however I still needed to get my dress altered, and my veil stayed behind at the store. I immediately called David's bridal and desperately asked for help with my alterations since I no longer had a store. The woman talked to the manager in the alterations department (who I later met, Rosa) and said they would help. From the moment I walked in, they were all so helpful and understanding of my frustration. I worked with Rosa every time I would go in. She would give me her undivided attention every time. I never felt rushed, and even when I sprained my ankle, she told me to wait a few weeks to see if I could walk in my heels instead of just carelessly just handing me my dress. < Review>
Let me start with I am most grateful to Aileen for such great costumer service!

I had a moment where no bride wants to beüò†üò¢
I went in for my first fitting in alterations, I had the vision in my head of how my dream dress should fit me, but the seamstress had a complete different one. I'm petite size 2 and on the short side 5'1 so I'm aware that most gowns are designed for tall. With that being said I had my idea of what i thought could be done so that the drop and fit of this mermaid/fitandflare gown would be right for me, but all i got was a big "No!" Let's just say we weren't meeting eye to eye on this. So of course, with my wedding being next month(felt pressured) I thought to myself let me just let her do what she says she's done before with this gown. So I paid and left her the gown and went home.(big mistake! Don't Ever Give in Brides! This is our Big Day! It's Our Gown!)
So next morning, I gave them a call to stop the alteration process (Aileen answered) I explained to her why, her tone of voice and apologizing made me feel good about coming back and seeing a different seamstress( I still felt overwhelmed and unsure if this next lady would see my vision and understand my body)
Well as I walk in I was greeted and walked to alterations met with Dolores and she's such a nice lady understood everything and agreed because of my height the drop needs to be a bit higher so I'm able to walk normally instead of doing the penguin walk üòÇ all she had to do is confirm with another awesome seamstress Chi if it will be possible? Chi's answer "Absolutely! What the bride wants, we will do" Wow! that's all i needed to hear! They will be altering my gown to look like my dream dressüòç
p.s I'm a size 2 with cup 32 C with a 0 waist that's why taking it in and giving it shape was a must!
5'1 height in mermaid/fitandflare drop was on my knee that's why raising the drop was also a must so Im able to walk!

Well Aileen, Dolores, and Chi Thank you so much! I'm now excited and can't wait for my last fitting!üë∞üòç

Overall my experience here was excellent because of customer service! (maybe the seamstress I met with the day before was just not having a good day) & Yes I could've spoke up the first time but after getting a few "No's!" knowing myself its best to go home and return at a later time üòÇ
So, Ladies if something isn't right or someone is just not seeing eye to eye with you speak up or run for Aileen! Lol üòÇ<//Review>
